a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x c :: real and f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = c * x powr 3 - 9 * x + 3"
and h1 : "f 2 = 9"
shows  "c = 3"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Given $f(x)=cx^3-9x+3$ and $f(2)=9$, find the value of $c$. The final Answer is 3
 ### Proof
 Plugging $x=2$ into the expression for $f(x)$, we find $f(2)=c(2^3)-9(2)+3=8c-18+3=8c-15$. Since we know that $f(2)=9$, \begin{align} f(2)&= 9 \\\Rightarrow\qquad8c-15&=9 \\\Rightarrow\qquad8c&=24 \\\Rightarrow\qquad c&=\boxed{3}
 \end{align}
 *)

theorem
fixes x c :: real and f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = c * x powr 3 - 9 * x + 3"
and h1 : "f 2 = 9"
shows  "c = 3"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
